sada khush raho

pti ptnii aane vaale kisii tyohaar kii kh'riidaarii ko lekr bhut jldiibaajii meN aurr bhut utsuk the  / 

pti ne ptnii se khaa, "j'ldii kro, mere paas ttaaiim nhiiN hai aurr bhii jrurii kaam hai oNphis kaa  / "

donoN taiyaar hokr ghr se niklne lge ....

tbhii baahr braamde meN baitthii buurhii maaN pr uske bette kii nj'r pdddh gii  / 

vh maaN ke paas jaakr bolaa, "maaN, hm log tyohaar kii kh'riidaarii ke lie baaj'aar jaa rhe haiN /  aapko kuch caahie to mujheN btaa diijie pliij  / 

maaN ne khaa.. mujhe kuch nhiiN caahie bettaa... / "

bette ke baar baar bhut j'or dekr khne pr maaN bolii, "tthiik hai, tum ruko, maiN abhii tumheN likh kr detii huuN / 

uske kuch der baad maaN ne bette ko kuch likhkr ek kaagz thmaa dii  / 

bettaa gaadddhii ke ddraaiviNg siitt pr baitthte hue apnii ptnii se bolaa, "dekhaa, maaN ko bhii kuch caahie thaa, pr bol nhiiN rhii thiiN /  mere j'id krne pr listt bnaa kr dii hai /  rottii aur vstr ke alaavaa bhii iNsaan ko jiivn meN bhut kuch caahie hotaa hai / "

acchaa baabaa tthiik hai, pr phle maiN apnii j'ruurt kaa saaraa saamaan luuNgii  /  baad meN aap apnii maaN kii listt dekhte rhnaa....ptnii bolii  / 

donoN gaadddhii se baazaar ke lie nikl pdddhe / 

caar ghNtto tk puurii kh'riidaarii krne ke baad ptnii bolii, "ab maiN bhut thk gyii huuN, maiN kaar meN esii claa kr baitthtii huuN, aap apnii maaN kaa saamaan unkaa listt dekh kr khriid lo / " maaN ne is tyohaar pr kyaa mNgaayaa hai...jraa mujheN bhii btaanaa ?

pti ne maaN kaa diyaa huaa kaagj ptnii ko hii pkdddhaa dii / 

baap re! itnii lNbii listt, . ptaa nhiiN kyaa kyaa mNgaayaa  hai ? aur bno shrvnn kumaar, khte hue ptnii gusse se pti kii or dekhne lgii aurr vaaps use listt pkdddhaa dii  / 

pr ye kyaa?

pti kii aaNkhoN meN aaNsuu........ aur listt pkdd'e hue haath suukhe ptte kii trh kaaNp rhaa thaa..... uskaa puuraa shriir besudh thaa / 

uskii ptnii b

hut ghbraa gyii /  kyaa huaa, aisaa kyaa maaNg liyaa hai tumhaarii maaN ne ? khkr pti ke haath se prcii jhptt lii....

hairaan thii ptnii bhii ...kyoNki itnii bdd'ii prcii meN bs cNd shbd hii likhe the.....

us kaagz meN likhaa thaa....

" mere kleje ke ttukdddhe, mere aaNkhoN ke taare,mere pyaare bettaa.. mujhe is tyohaar pr kyaa ,kisii bhii tyohaar pr kbhii kuch nhiiN caahie /  phir bhii tum j'id kr rhe ho to......ydi tumhaare shhr kii kisii dukaan meN agr mil jaae to ph'urst ke kuch pl mere lie lete aanaa....kyoNki ddhltii huii saaNjh huuN ab maiN , mujhe ghraate aNdhiyaare se ddr lgne lgaa hai ,mujheN akelaapn se ddr lgne lgaa hai, meraa ye burhaapaa mujheN kaatttaa hai, mujheN ab tnhaaii se ddr lgne lgaa hai ,to jb tk maiN jiNdaa huuN ,jbtk merii saaNse cl rhii hai, jbtk merii dhdddhknoN meN aavaaz hai,kuch pl baitthaa kr mere paas, kuch der ke lie hii shii baaNtt liyaa kr mere buddh'aape kaa akelaapn.... bin diip jlaae hii raushn ho jaaegii merii jiivn kii kaalii saaNjh.... kitne saal ho ge bettaa tujhe sprsh nhiiN kiyaa /  ek baar phir se, aa merii god meN apnaa sir rkh aur maiN mmtaa bhrii hthelii se shlaauuN tere sir ko  /  ek baar phir se itraae meraa hRdy mere apnoN ko k'riib, bhut k'riib paa kr.... aur muskuraa kr miluuN maut ke gle .... kyaa ptaa agle tyohaar tk rhuuN naa rhuuN........!!

donoN rone lge.....

..............
dostoN....hmaare maataa pitaa ko sirf hmaaraa prem caahie hmaaraa saath caahie ,hmaaraa aadr aurr smmaan caahie  / aurr kuch nhiiN bs.......!!

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
always stay happy

The husband and wife were in a hurry and very eager to make purchases for some upcoming festival.

The husband said to his wife, "Hurry up, I don't have time and I have other important office work."

Both of them got ready and started leaving the house.

Then her son's eyes fell on the old mother sitting outside in the verandah.

He went to his mother and said, "Mother, we are going to the market for festival shopping. If you want anything, please let me know."

Mother said... I don't want anything son..."

When the son repeatedly insisted, the mother said, "Okay, you wait, I will write to you right now.

After some time, the mother wrote something and handed a paper to the son.

While sitting on the driving seat of the car, the son said to his wife, "Look, mother also wanted something, but she was not saying. On my insistence, she has made a list. Apart from food and clothes, a person needs many things in life. Something is needed."

Okay Baba, okay, but first I will take all the things I need. Later you keep looking at your mother's list...wife said.

Both of them left for the market in the car.

After doing all the shopping for four hours, the wife said, "Now I am very tired, I sit in the car with the AC on, you buy your mother's stuff after looking at her list." What has mother ordered for this festival...please tell me too?

The husband handed over the paper given by his mother to his wife.

Oh My God! Such a long list. Don't know what has been ordered? And become Shravan Kumar, saying this the wife started looking at her husband angrily and handed him the list back.

But what is this?

There were tears in the husband's eyes... and the hand holding the list was trembling like a dry leaf... his whole body was unconscious.

his wife b

Hutt got scared. What happened, what has your mother asked for? Saying this she snatched the slip from her husband's hand...

The wife was also surprised... because only a few words were written in such a big slip...

It was written in that paper...

"The pieces of my heart, the stars of my eyes, my dear son... I don't want anything on any festival, let alone on this festival. Still, you are insisting... If any of your city's If you find me in the shop, then take some moments of leisure for me... because now it is evening, I am beginning to fear the deepening darkness, I am beginning to fear loneliness, this old age of mine bites me, Now I am afraid of loneliness, so as long as I am alive, as long as I am breathing, as long as there is sound in my heartbeats, sit with me for a few moments, even if only for a while, share the loneliness of my old age. .... Without lighting the lamp, the dark evening of my life will become bright... Son, it has been so many years that I have not touched you. Once again, come and put your head in my lap and I will caress you with my loving palm. To the head. Once again my heart should be proud of finding my loved ones close, very close... and I will meet death with a smile... who knows whether I will survive till the next festival or not... !!

Both of them started crying...

,
Friends... our parents only need our love, our support, our respect and honor. Nothing else but that...!!

featured_reviews.review_id: This is a large mosque built at an elevation of about fifteen feet from the ground and quite large. Our guide told us that it took twenty five years to build it. There is a lot of minute work on the minarets as well as inside the mosque. On the roof, on can see very intricate art work similar that seen in Jain temples. There is a unique prayer hall for women in that mosque. There is a well-maintained garden and it is a UNESCO heritage structure. Well-worth visiting!
